---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

export const prerender = true;

const lastUpdated = "April 2, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service — Visupair"
  description="Simple terms for using the Visupair website, account, store purchases, and creative services."
>
  <div class="account-page">
    <div class="legal-island">
      <article class="legal-page">
    <header class="legal-header">
      <p class="legal-kicker">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="legal-title">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </header>

    <div class="legal-body">
      <p>
        These Terms of Service (“Terms”) govern your use of the website and
        services operated by <strong>Visupair</strong> at
        <a href="https://visupair.com">visupair.com</a>. By using the site,
        creating an account, or placing an order, you agree to these Terms. If
        you do not agree, do not use the site.
      </p>

      <h2>1. What Visupair offers</h2>
      <p>
        Visupair is a creative studio and online store. You may use the site to
        browse Visupair’s work, buy <strong>physical</strong> and
        <strong>digital</strong> products, request <strong>creative services</strong>,
        and manage your account. Details about deliverables, timelines, and
        revisions appear on the relevant product or service page or in messages
        between you and Visupair.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Accounts</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Some features require an account (for example purchases, downloads,
          or favorites).
        </li>
        <li>
          You may be able to sign in with <strong>email and password</strong> or
          through a <strong>third-party account</strong> (such as social
          sign-in). That provider’s terms and privacy notice apply to the
          sign-in step.
        </li>
        <li>
          Keep your login details confidential and notify Visupair promptly at
          <a href="mailto:info@visupair.com">info@visupair.com</a> if you
          suspect unauthorized use. You are responsible for activity under
          your account until you do so, within reason.
        </li>
        <li>
          Visupair may suspend or close an account if Visupair reasonably believes there is
          abuse, fraud, or material risk to the site or other users.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        For how Visupair uses personal data, see the
        <a href="/legal/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Orders, prices, and payment</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Visupair aims for accurate descriptions and prices. Visupair may refuse or cancel
          orders that are clearly mistaken (including obvious pricing errors). If
          Visupair cancels after you have paid, Visupair will refund you as described in the
          <a href="/legal/refund-policy">Refund Policy</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          Payments are handled by an <strong>independent payment provider</strong>.
          Visupair does not store your full card number on its systems; payment data is
          protected according to that provider’s practices and terms.
        </li>
        <li>
          You authorize Visupair (and the payment provider, as needed) to charge your
          selected method for the amounts shown at checkout, including applicable
          taxes and shipping where Visupair states them.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Digital and physical products</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Digital products</strong> are licensed as described on the
          product page. Unless Visupair states otherwise, you receive a non-exclusive
          license for use described there—for example personal or agreed
          commercial use. You may not resell, redistribute, or share files in a
          way that replaces buying from Visupair, or strip credits, watermarks, or
          license notices where Visupair includes them.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Physical products</strong> depend on availability, production,
          and shipping shown at checkout or on the product page. Risk of loss in
          transit follows the carrier’s terms unless mandatory law says
          otherwise.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Custom services</h2>
      <p>
        Commissioned or packaged services follow the scope, revisions, and fees
        on the service page or in a written agreement. You provide materials and
        feedback on time; your delays may shift delivery dates. Visupair keeps general
        methods and pre-existing know-how; you receive the deliverables Visupair
        agrees for your order unless the contract says otherwise.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>You agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Violate applicable law, infringe others’ rights, or misuse Visupair’s content,
          branding, or systems.
        </li>
        <li>
          Interfere with the site or other users (for example by hacking,
          scraping, or trying to overwhelm Visupair’s infrastructure).
        </li>
        <li>
          Use Visupair’s products or services to create unlawful, harassing, or
          deliberately misleading work.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Other providers</h2>
      <p>
        Like most online businesses, Visupair uses independent suppliers for payment,
        authentication, hosting, and related tasks. Those arrangements do not
        change these Terms. <strong>What personal data is processed, why, and your
        rights</strong> are set out in the
        <a href="/legal/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a> and
        <a href="/legal/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a>. Visupair is not liable for
        events caused solely by a supplier outside Visupair’s reasonable control, and
        Visupair does not guarantee uninterrupted service.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        Content on the site (including art, text, branding, and layout) belongs
        to Visupair or Visupair’s licensors unless marked otherwise. These Terms only
        grant the rights Visupair spells out (including digital licenses in
        section&nbsp;4).
      </p>

      <h2>9. Warranty and liability</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Visupair provides the site and products “as is,” to the extent the law
          allows. Visupair does not promise error-free or uninterrupted operation.
        </li>
        <li>
          Nothing here limits liability that <strong>cannot</strong> be limited
          under applicable law (including certain consumer rights in the EU, EEA,
          or UK).
        </li>
        <li>
          Except where the law forbids, Visupair is not liable for indirect damages,
          lost profits, or lost data. For a claim tied to a specific paid order,
          Visupair’s liability is generally limited to what you paid for that order.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>10. Refunds</h2>
      <p>
        Refunds and cancellations follow the
        <a href="/legal/refund-policy">Refund Policy</a>. If you are a consumer,
        statutory rights in your country may still apply—for digital content,
        withdrawal can be limited once delivery or performance has started with
        your consent, where the law allows.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Changes</h2>
      <p>
        Visupair may update these Terms by posting a new version and changing the date
        above. Where changes are material, Visupair may also notify you on the site or
        by email if Visupair has your address. Continued use after the effective date
        means you accept the updated Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of <strong>Poland</strong> (without
        regard to conflict-of-law rules), while <strong>mandatory consumer
        protections</strong> in your country of residence (for example in the
        EU, EEA, or UK) remain available where the law requires. Competent courts
        are generally those for Visupair’s place of business, subject to those consumer
        rules.
      </p>

      <h2>13. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms:
        <a href="mailto:info@visupair.com">info@visupair.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Same outer shell as account favorites (island block) */
  .account-page {
    padding: 0 12px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-island {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    min-height: calc(100vh - 420px);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: stretch;
    padding: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2.75rem) clamp(1.1rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
  }

  .legal-page {
    width: 100%;
    /* Slightly wider measure; still capped for readability */
    max-width: min(90ch, 100%);
    margin-inline: auto;
    text-align: start;
    padding-block: 0.25rem 1rem;
    animation: legalFadeIn 0.45s ease-out;
    flex: 1;
  }

  @keyframes legalFadeIn {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(6px);
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }

  .legal-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.25rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    text-align: start;
  }

  .legal-kicker {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-title {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.25rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .legal-meta {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .legal-body {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.25vw + 0.96rem, 1.0625rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-secondary, var(--foreground));
    text-align: start;
    /* Comfortable paragraph width for long reads */
    overflow-wrap: break-word;
  }

  .legal-body h2 {
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 2.25rem 0 0.65rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .legal-body p {
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
  }

  .legal-body ul {
    margin: 0.25rem 0 1.25rem;
    padding-inline-start: 1.35rem;
    list-style-position: outside;
  }

  .legal-body li {
    margin: 0 0 0.55rem;
    padding-inline-start: 0.2rem;
  }

  .legal-body li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .legal-body a {
    color: var(--accent, #a78bfa);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .legal-body a:hover {
    opacity: 0.9;
  }
</style>
